# Arc: Other | Scene: NeitherPath4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Week had gone by since her brother had been taken hostage by Marion."
    new "Week had gone by since her brother had been taken hostage by Marion."

    old "Each day seemed to bring more dire news, more raids, more attacks, more setbacks."
    new "Each day seemed to bring more dire news, more raids, more attacks, more setbacks."

    old "But while the news of the country was dire, reports from lord Varga and her Spymaster Kravel seemed to indicate there was hope too."
    new "But while the news of the country was dire, reports from lord Varga and her Spymaster Kravel seemed to indicate there was hope too."

    old "The Rosannan army had been slow to mobilize, but was by now quickly gathering."
    new "The Rosannan army had been slow to mobilize, but was by now quickly gathering."

    old "Marion and the old houses had the advantage of their standing army of highly trained and well equipped soldiers, but they were few in numbers."
    new "Marion and the old houses had the advantage of their standing army of highly trained and well equipped soldiers, but they were few in numbers."

    old "The other noble houses, newer and more conscious of their status, had remained loyal to the crown."
    new "The other noble houses, newer and more conscious of their status, had remained loyal to the crown."

    old "This gave Sarah the advantage in numbers."
    new "This gave Sarah the advantage in numbers."

    old "The downside had been that though she had been able to call on the many noble houses, and rally their men to her flag, most of these men were not trained killers."
    new "The downside had been that though she had been able to call on the many noble houses, and rally their men to her flag, most of these men were not trained killers."

    old "They were, for the most part, farmers and craftsmen, called away from their work by their lords."
    new "They were, for the most part, farmers and craftsmen, called away from their work by their lords."

    old "This meant that it didn't just take longer to gather up the army, but they also required more training before they were battle ready."
    new "This meant that it didn't just take longer to gather up the army, but they also required more training before they were battle ready."

    old "Meanwhile, Marion's troops were burning the countryside, hoping that they could sow enough anger among the people to topple everything."
    new "Meanwhile, Marion's troops were burning the countryside, hoping that they could sow enough anger among the people to topple everything."

    old "Sarah understood Marion's strategy well enough."
    new "Sarah understood Marion's strategy well enough."

    old "If the people watched their homes and farmland burn, even if she was not to blame, they would sooner or later ask themselves what the royal family was doing for them."
    new "If the people watched their homes and farmland burn, even if she was not to blame, they would sooner or later ask themselves what the royal family was doing for them."

    old "And if the people stopped believing that the Rose family looked out for them, it wouldn't be long before they might begin to think of doing away with them."
    new "And if the people stopped believing that the Rose family looked out for them, it wouldn't be long before they might begin to think of doing away with them."

    old "All of that chaos, and Marion might never have to actually face her on the battlefield."
    new "All of that chaos, and Marion might never have to actually face her on the battlefield."

    old "To Sarah, this all meant that time was pressing."
    new "To Sarah, this all meant that time was pressing."

    old "The very thing she needed more of, she was quickly running out of."
    new "The very thing she needed more of, she was quickly running out of."

    old "How much longer?"
    new "How much longer?"

    old "Sarah, the units from the furthest provinces have arrived today."
    new "Sarah, the units from the furthest provinces have arrived today."

    old "But they have not yet been equipped. Hells, they haven't even begun to their basic training."
    new "But they have not yet been equipped. Hells, they haven't even begun to their basic training."

    old "If we send them out now, they'll serve as little more than bodies to absorb arrows."
    new "If we send them out now, they'll serve as little more than bodies to absorb arrows."

    old "Varga paused."
    new "Varga paused."

    old "If anything, they might actually weaken the army."
    new "If anything, they might actually weaken the army."

    old "Their morale is low, we've called them away from the fields during harvest season, many fear that their year's work will wither before they see home again."
    new "Their morale is low, we've called them away from the fields during harvest season, many fear that their year's work will wither before they see home again."

    old "Yes, lord Varga, I am aware."
    new "Yes, lord Varga, I am aware."

    old "Every decision I make seems to sow a thousand new disasters."
    new "Every decision I make seems to sow a thousand new disasters."

    old "Varga stepped forward."
    new "Varga stepped forward."

    old "Lady Sarah, that is not how I meant it."
    new "Lady Sarah, that is not how I meant it."

    old "Sarah waved her hands."
    new "Sarah waved her hands."

    old "Please, spare me the soft and kind words."
    new "Please, spare me the soft and kind words."

    old "When this war is won and over with, you can tell me all the kind things you want. For now I only want the truth."
    new "When this war is won and over with, you can tell me all the kind things you want. For now I only want the truth."

    old "Very well, then let me be honest."
    new "Very well, then let me be honest."

    old "There is a brief window available to us."
    new "There is a brief window available to us."

    old "A brief window where our troops will be ready to attack Marion's position, but where we might still end the uprising in time to spare the outer provinces from a wasted harvest."
    new "A brief window where our troops will be ready to attack Marion's position, but where we might still end the uprising in time to spare the outer provinces from a wasted harvest."

    old "We have to manage that tightrope."
    new "We have to manage that tightrope."

    old "They will not be as ready as they perhaps could have been, but they'll be as ready as we can make them, before our window closes."
    new "They will not be as ready as they perhaps could have been, but they'll be as ready as we can make them, before our window closes."

    old "Yes..."
    new "Yes..."

    old "Her voice drifted away."
    new "Her voice drifted away."

    old "Everything that I have available to you, every resource, I offer it to you. Just get the army ready in time."
    new "Everything that I have available to you, every resource, I offer it to you. Just get the army ready in time."

    old "I will move heaven and earth, lady Sarah."
    new "I will move heaven and earth, lady Sarah."

    old "Suddenly, the doors to the throne room burst open."
    new "Suddenly, the doors to the throne room burst open."

    old "One of the guards came marching in, dragging along a girl in peasant's clothing."
    new "One of the guards came marching in, dragging along a girl in peasant's clothing."

    old "The girl had a scared expression on her face."
    new "The girl had a scared expression on her face."

    old "Lady Rose!"
    new "Lady Rose!"

    old "The guard shoved the woman forward, causing her to near stumble down onto her feet."
    new "The guard shoved the woman forward, causing her to near stumble down onto her feet."

    old "We caught this spy undermining the castle."
    new "We caught this spy undermining the castle."

    old "Sarah rubbed her temples, more problems, just what she needed."
    new "Sarah rubbed her temples, more problems, just what she needed."

    old "Lord Varga, please resume your duties, this matter won't concern you."
    new "Lord Varga, please resume your duties, this matter won't concern you."

    old "Sarah could see in Varga's eyes a pity of the girl."
    new "Sarah could see in Varga's eyes a pity of the girl."

    old "Despite it, he bowed again, turned, and took his leave."
    new "Despite it, he bowed again, turned, and took his leave."

    old "Despite all of it, Sarah could see in the man that he never truly managed to shake the roots of his low birth."
    new "Despite all of it, Sarah could see in the man that he never truly managed to shake the roots of his low birth."

    old "On some level, he would always be more of a commoner than a nobleman, no matter his station or wealth."
    new "On some level, he would always be more of a commoner than a nobleman, no matter his station or wealth."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes back to the peasant girl and the guard."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes back to the peasant girl and the guard."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw movement."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw movement."

    old "Lady Carolyn had arrived, ahead of their budgetary meeting. Sarah had to figure out how to raise an army, as well as how to pay for one."
    new "Lady Carolyn had arrived, ahead of their budgetary meeting. Sarah had to figure out how to raise an army, as well as how to pay for one."

    old "Off on the other side, Sarah could see Lily, nearing closer to the throne as if there was any danger."
    new "Off on the other side, Sarah could see Lily, nearing closer to the throne as if there was any danger."

    old "Sarah didn't know if Lily was protecting her from the peasant or lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah didn't know if Lily was protecting her from the peasant or lady Carolyn."

    old "Tell me, what is this about?"
    new "Tell me, what is this about?"

    old "We found this...spy, infiltrating the castle supply room."
    new "We found this...spy, infiltrating the castle supply room."

    old "I'm not a spy!"
    new "I'm not a spy!"

    old "Off to her left, Sarah could see lady Carolyn, the same entertained smile on her face she always had, like she'd recalled a joke she wasn't about to share."
    new "Off to her left, Sarah could see lady Carolyn, the same entertained smile on her face she always had, like she'd recalled a joke she wasn't about to share."

    old "As much as Sarah respected her, she disliked how impossible she was to read."
    new "As much as Sarah respected her, she disliked how impossible she was to read."

    old "What happened, exactly?"
    new "What happened, exactly?"

    old "During a routine patrol, we came upon the kitchens, which were supposed to be empty at this time of the day."
    new "During a routine patrol, we came upon the kitchens, which were supposed to be empty at this time of the day."

    old "Responding to strange sounds, my men checked the cupboard where we found this individual, trying to steal as much food as she could carry."
    new "Responding to strange sounds, my men checked the cupboard where we found this individual, trying to steal as much food as she could carry."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes towards the girl."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes towards the girl."

    old "Is this true?"
    new "Is this true?"

    old "She could see the girl was trying to avoid meeting her gaze. She was no doubt scared out of her mind."
    new "She could see the girl was trying to avoid meeting her gaze. She was no doubt scared out of her mind."

    old "My...my lady...it's...some of it's true, yes, but not how he suggests it!"
    new "My...my lady...it's...some of it's true, yes, but not how he suggests it!"

    old "It's true that I was in the kitchen when I wasn't supposed to be, but I'm a servant in the castle!"
    new "It's true that I was in the kitchen when I wasn't supposed to be, but I'm a servant in the castle!"

    old "Are servants supposed to rob the food storage rooms?"
    new "Are servants supposed to rob the food storage rooms?"

    old "The girl turned her face down."
    new "The girl turned her face down."

    old "No...your highness...but..."
    new "No...your highness...but..."

    old "Sarah sighed. She had more to deal with than just this today."
    new "Sarah sighed. She had more to deal with than just this today."

    old "Out with it, please."
    new "Out with it, please."

    old "Well...I hadn't eaten in days..."
    new "Well...I hadn't eaten in days..."

    old "If you work as a servant, you are paid a fair wage, are you not?"
    new "If you work as a servant, you are paid a fair wage, are you not?"

    old "The girl nodded."
    new "The girl nodded."

    old "Then couldn't you use your wages to buy food at the market."
    new "Then couldn't you use your wages to buy food at the market."

    old "But your grace..."
    new "But your grace..."

    old "Ever since the war...the roads have become dangerous."
    new "Ever since the war...the roads have become dangerous."

    old "There aren't nearly as many merchants coming to market as before, and many farmers have held onto their food, fearing what the future might bring."
    new "There aren't nearly as many merchants coming to market as before, and many farmers have held onto their food, fearing what the future might bring."

    old "The girl suddenly stepped forward."
    new "The girl suddenly stepped forward."

    old "You grace, the prices of food have only gone up for weeks now."
    new "You grace, the prices of food have only gone up for weeks now."

    old "My wages...they used to be enough, but now, each week, it affords me and my family less and less."
    new "My wages...they used to be enough, but now, each week, it affords me and my family less and less."

    old "My husband has been drafted up into the army..."
    new "My husband has been drafted up into the army..."

    old "I'm the only one left to provide for my children..."
    new "I'm the only one left to provide for my children..."

    old "The girl's voice slowly dwindled."
    new "The girl's voice slowly dwindled."

    old "There it was, Sarah thought. The end result of all this war had brought."
    new "There it was, Sarah thought. The end result of all this war had brought."

    old "And despite how heavy it all weighed on her, the truth was that Sarah knew it was the ordinary people that paid the real prices."
    new "And despite how heavy it all weighed on her, the truth was that Sarah knew it was the ordinary people that paid the real prices."

    old "Sarah had never had to worry about whether or not she could eat for even a single day in her life."
    new "Sarah had never had to worry about whether or not she could eat for even a single day in her life."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard lady Carolyn speak softly besides the throne."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard lady Carolyn speak softly besides the throne."

    old "Sarah, I understand that her story plays on your soft nature."
    new "Sarah, I understand that her story plays on your soft nature."

    old "For as long as I've know you, you've had a kind heart."
    new "For as long as I've know you, you've had a kind heart."

    old "But things are different now."
    new "But things are different now."

    old "If the girl walks away, she will tell stories of what happened here today."
    new "If the girl walks away, she will tell stories of what happened here today."

    old "And so will the guard."
    new "And so will the guard."

    old "It won't be long before every servant in the castle will know that with a tear and a beg, they can stuff their faces full of food."
    new "It won't be long before every servant in the castle will know that with a tear and a beg, they can stuff their faces full of food."

    old "Lady Carolyn paused for a moment."
    new "Lady Carolyn paused for a moment."

    old "And once the food goes, soon will the rest. Silver, trinkets, relics."
    new "And once the food goes, soon will the rest. Silver, trinkets, relics."

    old "A castle is only as strong as the morale that rules it."
    new "A castle is only as strong as the morale that rules it."

    old "You're not a little girl anymore, you sit on the throne that your father once sat on."
    new "You're not a little girl anymore, you sit on the throne that your father once sat on."

    old "That means you must govern not just from your heart, but also from what is right for the country."
    new "That means you must govern not just from your heart, but also from what is right for the country."

    old "If this was not a time of war, perhaps you could give into your soft nature, but for now I council that you remain strong."
    new "If this was not a time of war, perhaps you could give into your soft nature, but for now I council that you remain strong."

    old "Sarah turned towards Carolyn."
    new "Sarah turned towards Carolyn."

    old "So what would you have me do? Throw this poor girl in prison?"
    new "So what would you have me do? Throw this poor girl in prison?"

    old "Carolyn shook her head."
    new "Carolyn shook her head."

    old "Nothing so drastic."
    new "Nothing so drastic."

    old "A few lashes will sort her out, and it will tell a different story to all the others that will think of stealing."
    new "A few lashes will sort her out, and it will tell a different story to all the others that will think of stealing."

    old "Off on her other side, she heard Lily move."
    new "Off on her other side, she heard Lily move."

    old "Sarah turned towards Lily and sighed."
    new "Sarah turned towards Lily and sighed."

    old "What is it?"
    new "What is it?"

    old "I don't think it's my place, lady Sarah..."
    new "I don't think it's my place, lady Sarah..."

    old "Sarah gestured with her hands, exhausted."
    new "Sarah gestured with her hands, exhausted."

    old "Please, if you're going to stand there like you have something to say, at least spit it out."
    new "Please, if you're going to stand there like you have something to say, at least spit it out."

    old "Lily cleared her throat."
    new "Lily cleared her throat."

    old "Well...Sarah, I think that it's just food."
    new "Well...Sarah, I think that it's just food."

    old "The war is hard on everyone, and she made a mistake. I don't think that needs anything more than a warning."
    new "The war is hard on everyone, and she made a mistake. I don't think that needs anything more than a warning."

    old "Sarah leaned back into the throne and began to contemplate."
    new "Sarah leaned back into the throne and began to contemplate."

    old "She needs to be made an example of"
    new "She needs to be made an example of"

    old "Sarah couldn't deny that in the grand scheme of things, some stolen food was hardly a problem."
    new "Sarah couldn't deny that in the grand scheme of things, some stolen food was hardly a problem."

    old "But Carolyn had raised some good points. If she let this go, where would it end?"
    new "But Carolyn had raised some good points. If she let this go, where would it end?"

    old "for now, she sat upon the throne, and with that came all the burdens of rulership. She couldn't only listen to her heart."
    new "for now, she sat upon the throne, and with that came all the burdens of rulership. She couldn't only listen to her heart."

    old "Guard, take her out back and give her five lashes."
    new "Guard, take her out back and give her five lashes."

    old "No! Please! I promise I won't ever do it again!"
    new "No! Please! I promise I won't ever do it again!"

    old "But it was too late for pleading now. The sentence had been spoken and there would be no going back."
    new "But it was too late for pleading now. The sentence had been spoken and there would be no going back."

    old "Gladly, my lady!"
    new "Gladly, my lady!"

    old "The guard seized the peasant girl by the arm and began to drag her away."
    new "The guard seized the peasant girl by the arm and began to drag her away."

    old "She kicked and screamed, but her small frame meant she could hardly stop the guard from dragging her, let alone pose a real threat to him."
    new "She kicked and screamed, but her small frame meant she could hardly stop the guard from dragging her, let alone pose a real threat to him."

    old "A few minutes later, Sarah would hear the cracking of the whip and the girl's screams, coming from the square just outside the castle."
    new "A few minutes later, Sarah would hear the cracking of the whip and the girl's screams, coming from the square just outside the castle."

    old "With each striking of the whip, another lash added to her back."
    new "With each striking of the whip, another lash added to her back."

    old "More than the wickedness of the whip, which the girl had earned, Sarah could also hear the cruel laughter of the gathered crowds."
    new "More than the wickedness of the whip, which the girl had earned, Sarah could also hear the cruel laughter of the gathered crowds."

    old "Floggings were a public affair, meant to in equal measure inflict pain and humiliation."
    new "Floggings were a public affair, meant to in equal measure inflict pain and humiliation."

    old "The girl would heal from the lashes, but Sarah doubted she would heal from the humiliation of it any time soon."
    new "The girl would heal from the lashes, but Sarah doubted she would heal from the humiliation of it any time soon."

    old "No time to feel regret now, Sarah concluded."
    new "No time to feel regret now, Sarah concluded."

    old "It was a small mistake, let it go"
    new "It was a small mistake, let it go"

    old "Sarah knew deep down that stome stolen food meant nothing, it likely wouldn't even interfere with dinner that evening."
    new "Sarah knew deep down that stome stolen food meant nothing, it likely wouldn't even interfere with dinner that evening."

    old "How could she punish a girl so seriously over something so small?"
    new "How could she punish a girl so seriously over something so small?"

    old "Listen to me very carefully."
    new "Listen to me very carefully."

    old "This was a mistake you made once, and one that you will make never again."
    new "This was a mistake you made once, and one that you will make never again."

    old "If you promise me this, then we can forget about this. But if you are ever caught again, there will be hell to pay, do you understand?"
    new "If you promise me this, then we can forget about this. But if you are ever caught again, there will be hell to pay, do you understand?"

    old "Yes!"
    new "Yes!"

    old "The girl nearly screamed out the word."
    new "The girl nearly screamed out the word."

    old "I promise I will never again do something so foolish."
    new "I promise I will never again do something so foolish."

    old "Thank you, lady Rose, I will remember your mercy for as long as I live!"
    new "Thank you, lady Rose, I will remember your mercy for as long as I live!"

    old "Sarah waved her hand, signalling she was done with the matter."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, signalling she was done with the matter."

    old "Guard, let her get back to work."
    new "Guard, let her get back to work."

    old "The guard seemed dissapointed that this was all that the matter would come to."
    new "The guard seemed dissapointed that this was all that the matter would come to."

    old "The room was now empty again, save for herself, lady Carolyn and Lily."
    new "The room was now empty again, save for herself, lady Carolyn and Lily."

    old "The room was now empty again, save for herself and Lady Carolyn."
    new "The room was now empty again, save for herself and Lady Carolyn."

    old "Well, now that we've settled that matter of great state importance, let's get started on that budget meeting."
    new "Well, now that we've settled that matter of great state importance, let's get started on that budget meeting."

    old "Lady Carolyn made a graceful bow and approached the throne."
    new "Lady Carolyn made a graceful bow and approached the throne."

    old "She handed Sarah a pile of documents."
    new "She handed Sarah a pile of documents."

    old "Lady Carolyn sat herself comfortable on the armrest of the throne."
    new "Lady Carolyn sat herself comfortable on the armrest of the throne."

    old "Nobody else in the castle, perhaps the country, would so comfortably violate protocol and think nothing of it."
    new "Nobody else in the castle, perhaps the country, would so comfortably violate protocol and think nothing of it."

    old "Going through the documents, Sarah tried to make sense of them."
    new "Going through the documents, Sarah tried to make sense of them."

    old "She'd studied enough math growing up that she could follow along, but it was clear that Lady Carolyn had a significant advantage on her in terms of knowledge."
    new "She'd studied enough math growing up that she could follow along, but it was clear that Lady Carolyn had a significant advantage on her in terms of knowledge."

    old "Her background as the master of the accounts and her family's background in banking and finance made her an expert in a field where Sarah was merely a novice."
    new "Her background as the master of the accounts and her family's background in banking and finance made her an expert in a field where Sarah was merely a novice."

    old "Sarah was happy for her skilled guidance, but she disliked just how much she had to rely on Lady Carolyn's good intentions."
    new "Sarah was happy for her skilled guidance, but she disliked just how much she had to rely on Lady Carolyn's good intentions."

    old "If Lady Carolyn wanted to manipulate the numbers ever so slightly, Sarah had no doubt that she'd be able to get away with it."
    new "If Lady Carolyn wanted to manipulate the numbers ever so slightly, Sarah had no doubt that she'd be able to get away with it."

    old "Who knew, perhaps she already did."
    new "Who knew, perhaps she already did."

    old "The meeting dragged and dragged, a consequence of the many complications brought about by the war."
    new "The meeting dragged and dragged, a consequence of the many complications brought about by the war."

    old "Lady Carolyn finally stood up after several hours."
    new "Lady Carolyn finally stood up after several hours."

    old "Lady Carolyn was the first to suggest wrapping up their meeting."
    new "Lady Carolyn was the first to suggest wrapping up their meeting."

    old "I think it's getting rather late."
    new "I think it's getting rather late."

    old "We ought to retire for the evening, though we're far from done I'm afraid."
    new "We ought to retire for the evening, though we're far from done I'm afraid."

    old "Sarah looked at Carolyn."
    new "Sarah looked at Carolyn."

    old "How much longer do you think?"
    new "How much longer do you think?"

    old "Lady Carolyn absently ran her fingers through the documents."
    new "Lady Carolyn absently ran her fingers through the documents."

    old "Nothing a few more hours won't fix."
    new "Nothing a few more hours won't fix."

    old "Sarah felt Lady Carolyn's hand fall on her shoulders."
    new "Sarah felt Lady Carolyn's hand fall on her shoulders."

    old "Tell you what, let's retire to my room, we'll have the servants bring up our food and we can work over dinner."
    new "Tell you what, let's retire to my room, we'll have the servants bring up our food and we can work over dinner."

    old "I'm sure with that we can put a wrap on it."
    new "I'm sure with that we can put a wrap on it."

    old "Lady Carolyn gestured towards Lily."
    new "Lady Carolyn gestured towards Lily."

    old "You can tell your little friend to take a break for the night."
    new "You can tell your little friend to take a break for the night."

    old "Sarah turned towards Lily."
    new "Sarah turned towards Lily."

    old "You can go ahead and retire for the night as well Lily."
    new "You can go ahead and retire for the night as well Lily."

    old "Lily eyed the both of them for a moment."
    new "Lily eyed the both of them for a moment."

    old "If...that is your order, I'll take my leave."
    new "If...that is your order, I'll take my leave."

    old "It is. Lady Carolyn's office is deep enough inside the castle that I doubt anyone could penetrate."
    new "It is. Lady Carolyn's office is deep enough inside the castle that I doubt anyone could penetrate."

    old "Very well, I will take my leave then."
    new "Very well, I will take my leave then."

    old "She bowed and turned, walking away."
    new "She bowed and turned, walking away."

    old "Getting up from the throne, Sarah followed Lady Carolyn down the hallways leading towards the council quarters where each of the council members held their office."
    new "Getting up from the throne, Sarah followed Lady Carolyn down the hallways leading towards the council quarters where each of the council members held their office."

    old "The sun was already setting, casting a golden light across the halls."
    new "The sun was already setting, casting a golden light across the halls."

    old "Usually, the castle was filled with life, a coming and going of nobles and commoners, each with their own reason for seeking an audience."
    new "Usually, the castle was filled with life, a coming and going of nobles and commoners, each with their own reason for seeking an audience."

    old "But ever since Marion had raised his banners, the castle had been forced to take its security more serious."
    new "But ever since Marion had raised his banners, the castle had been forced to take its security more serious."

    old "In addition, most noble families while still loyal, began to visit the castle less and less."
    new "In addition, most noble families while still loyal, began to visit the castle less and less."

    old "Everyone prayed for victory, but meanwhile, they planned for defeat. Each of them afraid to be seen as too loyalist, fearing what would happen to them if the Rose family collapsed."
    new "Everyone prayed for victory, but meanwhile, they planned for defeat. Each of them afraid to be seen as too loyalist, fearing what would happen to them if the Rose family collapsed."

    old "Plotting, Sarah thought, making sure they would survive no matter what side of the coin came up."
    new "Plotting, Sarah thought, making sure they would survive no matter what side of the coin came up."

    old "Sarah could hardly blame them, she would likely have done the same if she was in their position, but still she found their lack of genuine support painful."
    new "Sarah could hardly blame them, she would likely have done the same if she was in their position, but still she found their lack of genuine support painful."

    old "Painful and frightening, for so easily she could make a mistake and lose their support, and with it, everything."
    new "Painful and frightening, for so easily she could make a mistake and lose their support, and with it, everything."

    old "Are you alright?"
    new "Are you alright?"

    old "Excuse me?"
    new "Excuse me?"

    old "It's just, you haven't said a word since we left the throne room dear."
